"{\n  \"diabetes_mellitus\": {\n    \"Electronic Health Records\": {\n      \"description\": \"Electronic health records encompass structured and unstructured data, including demographics, diagnoses (ICD codes), medication history, and lab results, providing a longitudinal view of patient care for diabetes management.\"\n    },\n    \"Continuous Glucose Monitoring (CGM) Data\": {\n      \"description\": \"CGM data represents real-time glucose readings collected by wearable sensors, offering insights into glycemic trends, patterns, and variability in individuals with diabetes.\"\n    },\n    \"Medical Imaging (Retinal Fundus Photography)\": {\n      \"description\": \"Retinal fundus photography captures images of the retina to assess for diabetic retinopathy, a common complication of diabetes, allowing for early detection and monitoring of disease progression.\"\n    },\n    \"Genomic Data (Single Nucleotide Polymorphisms - SNPs)\": {\n      \"description\": \"Genomic data, specifically Single Nucleotide Polymorphisms (SNPs), can be used to identify genetic predispositions and risk factors associated with the development and progression of diabetes and its complications.\"\n    },\n    \"Clinical Notes (Natural Language Processing)\": {\n      \"description\": \"Clinical notes, processed through natural language processing (NLP) techniques, extract valuable information about patient symptoms, treatment responses, and lifestyle factors that may not be readily available in structured data.\"\n    }\n  }\n}"